{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b536da68-b194-4efb-83fd-7559bf6511ec","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the file order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_0LNlF8WdDYO0EmuUihtNhl","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-1390070610624fef82554fce679d63c8/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-1390070610624fef82554fce679d63c8/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"6c8acc6a-23de-417e-a7da-977aafbf7b40","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. Services.fs\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should come last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n2. Services.fs\n\n\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":441,"requestId":"5C02:16D25D:1D130C9:20E24FE:6A07C84D"},"id":"51e50833-66d8-4da7-a5e3-314a1812f8f9","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:28:52.810Z","parentId":"6e531237-195c-462f-a442-3af434d4d4b4"}
